Royal Media Services has appointed Linus Kaikai as the company's Editorial Director. His appointment was announced on Wednesday by Managing Director Wachira Waruru. "As Editorial Director, Linus will oversee the administrative and editorial functions of our news and current affairs operations across the RMS platforms," Waruru said. Prior to his appointment, KaikaiÂ was the Director of Strategy. He will replace Joe Ageyo who has served in the same capacity for the past four years. In a statement, RMS said that Ageyo had left the station to pursue his own interests. "I wish to announce that Joe Ageyo who has for the last four years served the RMS as Editorial Director is leaving the company to pursue other interests," Waruru said.